sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as TrustyAI Operator<br/>8080/8081/9443
    participant KServeIS as KServe InferenceService
    participant TASService as TrustyAI Service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>TLS 1.2+
    participant TASApp as TrustyAI App<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL / PVC
    participant LMESPod as LMES Evaluation Pod
    participant Driver as lmes-driver<br/>18080/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 / OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant EVRoute as EvalHub Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant EVRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>SAR + X-Tenant
    participant EVApi as EvalHub API<br/>8444/TCP HTTP
    participant GORCHRoute as GORCH Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GORCH as Orchestrator
    participant Generator as Generator IS
    participant Detector as Detector IS(s)

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over KServeIS,DB: Flow 1: TrustyAI Payload Interception (KServe)
        KServeIS->>TASService: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        TASService->>RBAC: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
        RBAC->>TASApp: Authorized request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (localhost)
        TASApp->>DB: Store payload data<br/>Conditional TLS
        DB-->>TASApp: Stored
        TASApp-->>RBAC: Response
        RBAC-->>TASService: Response
        TASService-->>KServeIS: 200 OK
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 230)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 2: LMEvalJob Execution
        User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>HTTPS TLS, RBAC
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Reconcile event
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Evaluation Pod<br/>ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI->>LMESPod: Pod scheduled
        Note over LMESPod,Driver: Init container copies driver binary<br/>to shared emptyDir volume
        LMESPod->>Driver: Start driver process
        Driver->>Driver: Execute python -m lm_eval<br/>subprocess
        Operator->>Driver: GET /GetStatus<br/>18080/TCP HTTP (pod-local)
        Driver-->>Operator: Progress update
        Driver->>S3: Upload results<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>AWS-style credentials
        S3-->>Driver: Upload confirmed
        Operator->>Driver: POST /Shutdown<br/>18080/TCP HTTP
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,EVApi: Flow 3: EvalHub Multi-Tenant Evaluation
        User->>EVRoute: POST evaluation request<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS (reencrypt)
        EVRoute->>EVRBAC: Forward<br/>kube-rbac-proxy SAR
        Note over EVRBAC: SAR check with<br/>X-Tenant namespace scoping
        EVRBAC->>EVApi: Authorized<br/>8444/TCP HTTP (localhost)
        EVApi->>K8sAPI: Create Job<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>EVApi: Job created
        Note over LMESPod: Evaluation Job Pod runs
        LMESPod->>EVApi: POST status events<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service CA)<br/>Bearer token
        EVApi-->>User: Evaluation results
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 240)
        Note over User,Detector: Flow 4: GuardrailsOrchestrator Auto-Config
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch InferenceServices<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: InferenceService list<br/>(generators + detectors)
        Operator->>Operator: Generate ConfigMap<br/>(auto-config)
        User->>GORCHRoute: Request with content<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS (edge/reencrypt)
        GORCHRoute->>GORCH: Forward<br/>Conditional kube-rbac-proxy
        GORCH->>Generator: Send to generator IS<br/>HTTPS/HTTP Conditional TLS
        Generator-->>GORCH: Generated response
        GORCH->>Detector: Send to detector IS(s)<br/>HTTPS/HTTP Conditional TLS
        Detector-->>GORCH: Detection results
        GORCH-->>GORCHRoute: Guardrailed response
        GORCHRoute-->>User: Safe response
    end
